To properly lower your body during the One-Arm Push-Up, follow these steps:

* Start in a push-up position with one hand behind your back.
* Slowly lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
* Keep your core engaged and your body in a straight line from head to heels.
* Avoid letting your hips sag or your back arch.
* Lower yourself slowly and control your descent to maintain proper form.

Remember to focus on slow and controlled movements to target the correct muscle groups and avoid injury.
